==English==

===Etymology===
From {{suffix|en|acid|ify}}, from {{uder|en|la|acidus||sour, acid}}; compare {{cog|fr|acidifier}}.

===Pronunciation===
{{rfp|en}}
* {{audio|en|En-us-acidify.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb}} {{tlb|en|transitive}}

# To make something (more) [[acidic]] or [[sour]]; to convert into an [[acid]].
# To [[neutralize]] [[alkali]]s.
#: ''to '''acidify''' sugar''
# {{lb|en|figurative}} To sour; to [[embitter]].
#* {{RQ:Carlyle French Revolution}}
#*: His thin existence all '''acidified''' into rage.

